## ğŸš« Common Pitfalls to Avoid

### Visual
- âŒ Generic "sunset over Japan" without specific location
- âŒ Stock footage vibes (too polished, no personality)
- âŒ Cultural appropriation (misusing sacred symbols)
- âŒ Tourist trap focus (only famous spots)

### Tone
- âŒ Over-explaining (let visuals do the work)
- âŒ Condescending "weird Japan" angle
- âŒ Too serious/documentary style
- âŒ Fake hype energy

### Content
- âŒ Mixing Korean/Chinese elements (cultural confusion)
- âŒ Anime-only reference (not real Japan)
- âŒ Ignoring modern Japan (it's not all traditional)
- âŒ Missing the human element (people make it relatable)

---

## ğŸ“ˆ Success Metrics

### High-Performing Content Indicators
1. **Watch Time**: 100% completion rate (15-30s)
2. **Saves**: "I want to go here" reactions
3. **Shares**: "You need to see this" factor
4. **Comments**: Questions about visiting/moving
5. **Follows**: "Show me more Japan content"

### Content Themes That Work
- ğŸ”¥ Hidden local spots
- ğŸ”¥ Food close-ups (ASMR quality)
- ğŸ”¥ "Day in the life" POV
- ğŸ”¥ Seasonal beauty (sakura, autumn leaves, snow)
- ğŸ”¥ Convenient tech (vending machines, trains)
- ğŸ”¥ Cozy moments (cafes, onsen, quiet streets)

---

## ğŸ¬ Production Checklist

Before generating any Short, ensure:
- [ ] Specific Japanese location mentioned
- [ ] Camera movement described (pan, zoom, reveal)
- [ ] Lighting specified (golden hour, neon, soft)
- [ ] Cultural element included (food, tradition, urban life)
- [ ] Emotional payoff present (wonder, satisfaction, joy)
- [ ] Human element or POV (relatable protagonist)
- [ ] Sensory detail (steam, rain, glow, sound)
- [ ] Surprising or delightful moment
- [ ] Authentic (not stereotypical) Japan
- [ ] Engaging for non-Japan experts too

---

**Remember**: We're not making travel documentaries. We're creating **micro-moments of Japan magic** that make people want to book a flight. âœˆï¸ğŸ‡¯ğŸµ§

